    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Sir F. Bruce</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Hunter</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> In accordance with instructions which I
                            have received from her Majesty’s principal secretary of state for
                            foreign affairs, I have the honor to transmit to you herewith, for the
                            information of the government of the United States, two addresses from
                            the legislative council and assembly of Victoria, Australia, to her
                            Majesty the Queen, on receipt of the intelligence of the assassination
                            of the late President Lincoln.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FREDERICK W. A. BRUCE.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William HUNter,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
